## Why This Is Asked
Tests mastery of SavedModel signatures, multi-inputs, and feature routing in TF Serving for real-world multimodal models.

## Key Concepts
- tf.saved_model.save with multiple signatures
- tf.functions with input_signature using dict inputs
- tf.TensorSpec for inputs
- signature-based routing in TF Serving
- model versioning and backward compatibility

## Code Example
```javascript
// Pseudo Python/TensorFlow example illustrating exported signatures
import tensorflow as tf

class M(tf.keras.Model):
    def call(self, inputs):
        img, txt = inputs['image'], inputs['text']
        return tf.concat([self.image_net(img), self.text_net(txt)], axis=-1)

@tf.function(input_signature=[{'image': tf.TensorSpec([None,224,224,3], tf.float32),
                              'text': tf.TensorSpec([None,128], tf.float32)}])
def serving_default(inputs):
    return {'pred': model(inputs)}

@tf.function(input_signature=[{'text': tf.TensorSpec([None,128], tf.float32)}])
def predict_dense(inputs):
    return {'pred': model(inputs['text'])}

tf.saved_model.save(model, export_dir, signatures={'serving_default': serving_default,
                                                'predict_dense': predict_dense})
```

## Follow-up Questions
- How would you handle optional inputs or feature versioning in TF Serving?
- How would you test that both signatures stay in sync during deploys?

## Why This Is Asked

Assess ability to design production-ready, self-healing inference pipelines, with drift detection and safe rollback in TF Serving.

## Key Concepts

- Drift metrics: KL divergence on input features and model-proxy accuracy/latency proxies
- Canary rollout and automatic rollback
- Per-model baselines, rolling windows, alerting, and audit logs

## Code Example

```javascript
// Pseudocode for drift check and rollback trigger
function evaluateDrift(model, payload) {
  const dist = klDivergence(payload.features, model.baseline);
  const lat = measureLatency(model);
  const acc = approximateAccuracy(model, payload.labels);
  return (dist > model.driftThreshold) || (lat > model.latencyThreshold) || (acc < model.accuracyLowerBound);
}
```

## Follow-up Questions

- How to set drift thresholds? How to test rollback safely? How to handle cascading rollbacks across models?
